=======<br>
I dont know what dps/m is ment to be exactly (feel free to explain it a bit more). <br>
=======<br>
<br>
Damage per second per mana. But don't worry about it, we're not talking offense. That was merely a way of describing how mage pets being both O &amp; D makes them less powerful at both.<br>
<br>
I'm not unhappy about it. I'm just pointing out that if the enemy kills our offense, it kills our defense too. It's just another reason mage defense sucks, another reason to back up my claim that root is 1000x better than a pet, defensively.<br>
<br>
Basically, to explain it by comparing to root: If a wizard is primarily using root as his defense, and the root breaks, he still possesses 100% of his offensive power. <br>
<br>
When a pet dies, the magician loses a great deal of offensive power.<br>
<br>
So, while I don't think that that should be changed or anything, since it's what the basics of the mage class are all about, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I'm merely pointing it out for consideration when comparing a pet to root. Some say a pet is the best defense, and I use the above comparison to point out that pets are a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> very flawed defense.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
=========<br>
I realy wish you was right. It does happen now and then, and I am happy everytime it does. But its a rare event.<br>
=========<br>
<br>
I have played a level 30 paladin and a level 53 cleric. In both instances, root resists *extremely* rarely on low blues. The only time root breaking early is a problem is when the mob is very high blue, or in the case of the paladin yellow+. High MR mobs of course will resist more, but that's an obvious exception. Of course, nukes also give root another chance to break. Not much of a problem, just reroot. Low mana, fast cast. Your statement that it's a 'very rare event' is very misleading. It's not rare at all.<br>
<br>
More often than not, on any typical mob, root lasts the full duration. It will often fall a tick, maybe two short of max duration. For root to break on the first tick after being cast is by no means rare, but uncommon compared to the other options.<br>
<br>
Level 1 root anyway, I've never been fewlish enough to use any other. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109465>~Krilen</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 194<br> <font color=#333333>(9/14/02 5:46:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summoned item with root</span><hr size=1> Quote by Krilren:<br>
